    "narrative": "For April 23, 2026, the LawDog lineup is anchored by **Geraldo Perdomo**, our clear strongest play of the day with a 68.41 score. Leading off against Martin, **Geraldo Perdomo** benefits from a massive 17% SP skill advantage and a 10% boost from his spot at the top of the order, making him our primary engine for Runs and SB volume. **Bryson Stott** is our secondary anchor at 62.02; while he faces a solid arm in Cabrera, the combination of favorable wind and a 13% platoon boost elevates his floor well above his peers. We are cautiously optimistic about **Matt Chapman** (57.18), who earns a slight bump thanks to a slow delivery from Glasnow, which should provide a rare opportunity for him to pad our scarce SB category despite the tough matchup.\n\nThe benching of **Drew Gilbert** and **Wenceel Perez** highlights the scarcity-driven nature of our roster strategy today. **Drew Gilbert** (43.24) and **Wenceel Perez** (45.20) were the final cuts; while both occupy the lower rungs of the order, **Wenceel Perez** barely missed the cut due to his negative platoon dynamic against Sproat. With **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, **Cal Raleigh**, **Will Smith**, and **Lawrence Butler** all currently unavailable due to off-days or rest, we are running thin. We must remain vigilant regarding the Glasnow start against **Luis Arraez**, **Matt Chapman**, **Drew Gilbert**, and **Jung Hoo Lee**; facing an elite arm like his remains a significant drag on our ceiling. Despite the lack of power upside from **Luis Arraez** (54.16), his presence remains vital for AVG, even if his 54.16 score suggests a marginal day overall. Keep a close eye on any late lineup changes for **Jung Hoo Lee**, as his 10% platoon boost is essential for maintaining our efficiency targets.",
